going_public_at":"2018-04-30T18:14:57.323Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"1、\nLogin to your GitLab account and create a new project, then go to--\u003e\u003ehttps://gitlab.com/{username}/{project}}/settings/integrations\n\n2、\nYou can add url to ssrf.following are the steps to reproduce:\n\nIf you enter http://127.0.0.1:80/haha.txt as url,we will get --\u003e\u003eHook executed successfully but returned HTTP 404 \u003chtml\u003e \u003chead\u003e\u003ctitle\u003e404 Not Found\u003c/title\u003e\u003c/head\u003e \u003cbody bgcolor=\"white\"\u003e \u003ccenter\u003e\u003ch1\u003e404 Not Found\u003c/h1\u003e\u003c/center\u003e \u003chr\u003e\u003ccenter\u003enginx/1.12.1\u003c/center\u003e \u003c/body\u003e \u003c/html\u003e\n\n\n\nIf you enter http://127.0.0.1:9200/haha.txt as url, we will get --\u003e\u003eHook execution failed: Failed to open TCP connection to 127.0.0.1:9200 (Connection refused - connect(2) for \"127.0.0.1\" port 9200)\n(indicating that the port is actually closed.)\n\nThe test was done on https://gitlab.com/\n\n\bI did not do more test.Thanks\n\n## Impact\n\ncan scan the intranet to get sensitive information.","weakness":{"id":68,"name":"Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":251026,"file_name":"17_14_23__01_03_2018.jpg","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/251/026/eab830b962e5f8350b75da0cca4ea44ff987499b/17_14_23__01_03_2018.jpg?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%2217_14_23__01_03_2018.jpg%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%2717_14_23__01_03_2018.jpg\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fjpeg\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQYJPM5INV%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T095523Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECgaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJGMEQCI